PARAGRAPH.#text: Spectra Energy Corp.'s SE profit fell 24% in the second quarter as sales slumped in all of the company's segments on lower commodity prices. The operator of natural-gas pipelines and storage facilities has seen low commodity prices as strong headwinds to its results. Companies like Spectra had benefited in recent quarters from a North American shale drilling boom, although the effect of intense production on natural gas prices has recently moved many players to rein in activity. Spectra reported a profit of $215 million, or 33 cents a share, compared with a year-earlier profit of $284 million, or 44 cents a share.
